Which configuration option with a Docker configuration shows the ports that will beopened when the image is started?
A)  PORT
B)  EXPOSE
C)  OPEN
D)  LISTEN
B
B. The EXPOSE configuration option indicates ports and protocols to be opened. Theseoptions can also be given on the command line at runtime by using the - p option. Theports to be exposed can also be found when running the inspect command and are listedas ExposedPorts within the output.
